Package: tikzomr
Title: Read TikZ-Generated Mark Sheets into CSV
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Koji E.", "Kosugi", email = "kosugitti@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Create mark sheets with TeX/TikZ and read scanned sheets into a
    response data frame. Uses four corner fiducials for alignment (a projective
    homography solved from the fiducial correspondence) and a fill-ratio test
    per bubble. Runs entirely locally, so answer sheets never leave the machine.
    The reading definition is derived from the same layout used to typeset the
    sheet, so there is no manual placement of read positions.
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
Imports:
    magick,
    pdftools,
    utils
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
